abstract: A fall of coal occurred in the pit of Roche-laMoliere, near Saint-Etienne, (Loire,) on May 8, by which three workmen, Brossard and the two brothers Peyron, were cut off from all communication with the surface. As hopes were entertained that they were solely imprisoned, and not crushed, gangs of men were at once organized to liberate them, and those efforts happily proved successful after the poor men had passed 125 hours in their subterranean prison.

abstract: LONDON, June 4.--The Daily News has a Bucharest dispatch saying that the Danube is still impassable. Rarely has the water risen so high at this season, and this merely with rain. Farias.
